text: Kiune Fletcher (born 14 May 2002) is a Trinidad and Tobago female volleyball player. She was part of the Trinidad and Tobago women's national volleyball team. She participated in the 2017 FIVB Volleyball World Grand Prix and 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. == References == == Other websites == * Fletcher fires women to first win, Guardian Media Dec 09 2019 Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Trinidad and Tobago volleyball players
